# Secrets & Google Exposure (Public Repo)

This repo is **public**. Treat cloud credentials like house keys — never put them in git, chat, PRs, or docs.

## Never commit or paste real values
- `.env`, `.env.*` (except `.env.example` with **placeholders only**)
- `gas/secrets.local.md` (use `gas/secrets.local.md.example` only)
- Live `EXPO_PUBLIC_GAS_WEB_APP_URL` (`script.google.com/macros/s/.../exec`)
- Real `EXPO_PUBLIC_DEFAULT_DRIVE_FOLDER_ID` or Drive folder URLs with real ids
- OAuth client secrets, refresh tokens, API keys, Spreadsheet ids used in production
- Built APK/AAB/IPA artifacts (they can embed `EXPO_PUBLIC_*`)

## Agent must actively stop the user
- If the user asks to **commit**, **push**, or **paste into README/issues/PRs** anything that looks like a live Web App URL, Drive folder id, or `.env` contents → **refuse**, explain why, and suggest placeholders.
- Before any `git commit` / `git add`, check the staged set. If `.env`, secrets files, or real `/exec` URLs appear → **block** and warn.
- Never echo the user’s real `.env` values back in chat. Refer to keys by **name** only (e.g. “your Web App URL”).
- In docs/examples/code comments, use only placeholders:
  - `https://script.google.com/macros/s/your-deployment-id/exec`
  - `THIS_IS_THE_FOLDER_ID`

## Mental model (remind when relevant)
- **Public clone ≠ Google access** — only if secrets stay out of git.
- Spreadsheet/folder “only me” does **not** protect the Web App; the `/exec` URL is the real door (script runs as the owner).
- `EXPO_PUBLIC_*` is git-safe when local, but **baked into the app binary** — don’t redistribute builds that contain live URLs.

## Safe defaults in advice
- Keep Sheet + photos folder **Restricted / only owner**.
- If a live `/exec` URL may have leaked: tell the user to **redeploy** (new URL) and update local `.env` — never put the new URL in the repo.
